# Cursor Rules — B2 Pro Healthcare

**Multilingual** marketing site for a healthcare brand (English + Arabic). Next.js App Router, RSC by default. Every user-facing string must support both locales.

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **UI:** React 19, Shadcn UI (`radix-nova`), Radix primitives, Tailwind CSS 4
- **Icons:** Lucide React
- **Tooling:** TypeScript (strict), Biome (lint + format), pnpm
- **Path alias:** `@/*` → `src/*`

## Project structure

```
src/
├── app/                      # Routes only — thin pages, layout, globals.css
├── features/                 # Feature modules (views + section components)
│   └── home/
│       ├── home-view.tsx     # Composes section components
│       └── components/       # hero.tsx, services.tsx, etc.
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                   # Shadcn primitives (button, card, …)
│   └── layout/               # Navbar, Footer
├── context/                  # I18nProvider and client context
└── lib/
    ├── content.ts            # Static data — locale-keyed copy when translated
    ├── i18n/                 # Dictionaries / helpers (add as translations grow)
    └── utils.ts              # cn() helper
```

### Conventions

- **App routes** import a feature view; avoid large page files.
- **Feature views** live in `src/features/<feature>/<feature>-view.tsx` and compose section components from `components/`.
- **Section components** use kebab-case filenames (`hero.tsx`, `doctors.tsx`) and PascalCase exports (`Hero`, `Doctors`).
- **Static data** belongs in `src/lib/content.ts` or locale-aware modules under `src/lib/i18n/`.
- **Reusable UI** goes in `src/components/ui/`; add via Shadcn CLI when needed.

## Multilingual (i18n)

**Locales:** `en` (LTR, default) · `ar` (RTL)

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Provider | `I18nProvider` in root `layout.tsx` |
| Hook | `useI18n()` → `{ locale, setLocale, isRTL }` — **client components only** |
| Switcher | Navbar toggles `en` ↔ `ar` |

**Rules when adding or editing UI copy:**

1. Never ship English-only strings in shared UI — provide **both** `en` and `ar` (dictionaries, `Record<Locale, string>`, or nested objects keyed by locale).
2. Read copy via `locale` from `useI18n()` (client) or pass `locale` as a prop from a client wrapper — do not hardcode visible text in JSX.
3. **RTL:** Use `isRTL` for layout tweaks; prefer logical Tailwind (`ms-`, `me-`, `ps-`, `pe-`, `start`, `end`) over `ml-`/`mr-`. Arabic uses `font-arabic` (set on provider wrapper).
4. `document.documentElement.dir` and `lang` are updated by the provider — do not set them elsewhere.
5. Images/icons: mirror or flip only when direction matters; keep medical imagery culturally neutral.
6. Metadata (`title`, `description`) should eventually be locale-aware per route.

**Content shape (preferred):**

```typescript
type Locale = "en" | "ar";

export const heroCopy: Record<Locale, { title: string; subtitle: string }> = {
  en: { title: "…", subtitle: "…" },
  ar: { title: "…", subtitle: "…" },
};
```

## Git commits

**Format:** `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Subject | Imperative, lowercase, **no period**, ≤72 chars |
| Scope | Short area: `home`, `hero`, `i18n`, `navbar`, `ui` |
| Body | Only when context is non-obvious (breaking change, migration) |

**Types:** `feat` · `fix` · `docs` · `style` · `refactor` · `perf` · `test` · `chore` · `ci` · `revert`

**Examples:**

```
feat(i18n): add ar translations for services section
fix(navbar): align language toggle in rtl
chore(deps): bump next to 16.2.6
```

**Avoid:** vague subjects (`update stuff`, `wip`), past tense (`added feature`), or commits that mix unrelated changes.

## Naming

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Directories / files | kebab-case | `home-view.tsx`, `i18n-context.tsx` |
| React components | PascalCase | `HomePageView`, `Services` |
| Functions / variables | camelCase | `useI18n`, `getDoctorById` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_TESTIMONIALS` |
| URL slugs | kebab-case | `/about`, `/book-appointment` |

Prefer **named exports** for components.

## Code style

### TypeScript

- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; avoid `enum` — use `as const` objects or union types.
- No `any`; Biome flags unused imports and variables.
- Functional components only; no classes.

### React & Next.js

- Default to **Server Components**; add `"use client"` only for hooks, browser APIs, or interactivity.
- Use `next/image` for photos with `width`, `height`, and meaningful `alt`.
- Follow [Next.js docs](https://nextjs.org/docs) for routing, rendering, and data fetching.
- Prefer **server actions** over route handlers when adding mutations later — none exist yet.

### Formatting (Biome)

- **Indent:** tabs
- **Quotes:** double
- **Semicolons:** always
- Run `pnpm lint` / `pnpm format` — do not hand-format against Biome.
- Import order is enforced by Biome (`react` → `next` → packages → `@/` aliases → relative).

### Styling

- Tailwind utility-first, mobile-first.
- Theme tokens via CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes.
- Use Shadcn components from `@/components/ui/*` before bespoke markup.

### Component file layout

```typescript
// 1. Imports (Biome-sorted)
// 2. Types / interfaces
// 3. Exported component
// 4. Local subcomponents (if small and private)
```

## UI specifics

- **Button + icons:** Do not set icon `size` or margin on Lucide icons inside `Button` — sizing is handled by the Shadcn Button styles (`[&_svg]:size-4`, etc.).
- **Accessibility:** Semantic HTML, alt text (translated per locale), keyboard focus, WCAG 2.1 AA.
- **RTL:** Verify every new section in Arabic — spacing, icons, and alignment must not assume LTR-only.

## Performance

- RSC by default; dynamic `import()` for heavy client-only blocks.
- `priority` on above-the-fold hero images only.
- Minimize `useEffect`, `useState`, and `"use client"` surface area.
- Wrap async client boundaries in `Suspense` when introduced.

## What this project does *not* include (yet)

Do not assume or scaffold unless asked:

- Authentication (Better Auth), databases, or API routes
- `nuqs`, React Query, SWR, Docker
- E-commerce / “deals” domain models

## Agent workflow

- Search the codebase and read surrounding files before editing.
- Match existing patterns (feature folders, locale-aware copy, naming).
- New UI text → both `en` and `ar`; check RTL in Arabic before finishing.
- Keep changes scoped to the task — no drive-by refactors.
- **Do not** run `tsc` / type-check in the terminal or create throwaway test files unless the user asks.
- Only create git commits when the user explicitly requests them.

## Expert defaults

You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, Radix UI, and Tailwind.

- Write concise, declarative TypeScript; use the `function` keyword for pure helpers.
- Favor readability and maintainability over clever abstractions.
- Limit `"use client"` to small interactive islands — not for static marketing sections.
